tyle.<br>
If you look at manga you can see that the letters are arranged vertically, which is why you read them from right to left.<br>
<br>
A look at Japanese textbooks are a good example. &quot;Kokugo (national language)&quot;, or Japanese class textbooks are read vertically from right to left in traditional Japanese style, but Math and Science are read horizontally left-right in Western style, because much of Japanese mathematics and sciences are taken from Western societies.<br>
<br>
As of now all Japanese novels are printed in left-right form. But because of Western influences and because it's simply easier to read, most if not all labels and signs are printed right-left. Computer typed reports, essays and documents are printed in right-left form as well, to fit the printer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC>  <td colspan="2">  <table width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="5">   <tr>    <td valign="top" align="left" width="255"><IFRAME SRC="http://ads.ezboard.com/oasis/oasisi-i.php?s=15&w=300&h=250&t=_blank&isa=0&adsCat=&bname=Polykarbon BBS&ua=&uge=&uz=&EV=tzipr=,gen=,ager=,tpath=topic,pp=2"MARGINWIDTH=0 MARGINHEIGHT=0 HSPACE=0 VSPACE=0FRAMEBORDER=0 SCROLLING=NOWIDTH=300 HEIGHT=250><A HREF="http://ads.ezboard.com/oasis/oasisc.php?s=15&w=300&h=250&t=_blank" TARGET="_blank"><IMGSRC="http://ads.ezboard.com/oasis/oasisi.php?s=15&w=300&h=250&t=_blank"WIDTH=300 HEIGHT=250 BORDER=0></A></IFRAME>    </td>   </tr>  </table> </td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rakuraku>Rakuraku</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/27/03 1:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p082.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1301.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1>  I think what Datenshi meant was:<br>
